> [Suggested description]
> Hitron HI3120 v7.2.4.5.2b1 allows stored XSS via the Parental Control
> option when creating a new filter. The device fails to properly handle
> inputs, allowing an attacker to inject and execute JavaScript.
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Vulnerability Type]
> Cross Site Scripting (XSS)
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Vendor of Product]
> Hitron
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Affected Product Code Base]
> Hitron HI3120 - 7.2.4.5.2b1
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Affected Component]
> Parental Control page
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Attack Vectors]
> A xss payload used in the following path: /webpages/index.html#page-security-parental-control/m/5/s/6
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Discoverer]
> Gregory Cardoso
>
> ------------------------------------------
